BookLibrary

Class Library

  • java.lang.Object
    • BookLibrary.Library

  • public class Library
extends java.lang.Object
    This class handles all the user commands These commands include adding, removing, checking out and returning a book.
    Author:
    Prachiti Atigre, Ujani Patel

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(Book book)
        Adds the book to the array of books Before adding, the growArraySize method is called to check if there is space in the array. Once there is space, the book is added
        Parameters:
        book - the book to be added

      • checkOut

        public boolean checkOut(Book book)
        Checks out the book from the library The find method is called to check if the book exists in the library. If it does, the getCheckedOut method is called to determine if the book has been already been checked out or not. The getCheckedOut method returns true if the book has been checked out and false otherwise. If it is true, the method returns false and true otherwise
        Parameters:
        book - the book to be checked out
        Returns:
        true if book has successfully been checked out and false otherwise

      • find

        private int find(Book book)
        Helper method to find a book in the bag Checks if the serial number of the book entered is equal to the serial number of any of the books already present in the array through the means of a for loop
        Parameters:
        book - the book to be found
        Returns:
        index number of the array at which the book is present if found, -1 otherwise

      • grow

        private void grow()
        Helper method to grow the capacity of the array by 4 The array has an initial capacity of 4, and it is automatically increased whenever full A new array is created and all the elements from the smaller array are copied to the new array

      • print

        public void print()
        Prints the list of all available books in the library

      • printByDate

        public void printByDate()
        Prints the list of all available books in the library in ascending order of the date the book was published

      • printByNumber

        public void printByNumber()
        Prints the list of all available books in the library in ascending order of the serial number of the book

      • remove

        public boolean remove(Book book)
        Removes the book from the array of books The find method is called to check exists in the library (What if the book has been checked out?), If the book is found, the shiftArray method is called to get rid of the book
        Parameters:
        book - the book to be removed
        Returns:
        true if book is found, false otherwise

      • returns

        public boolean returns(Book book)
        Returns the book to the library The find method is called to check if the book exists in the library. If it does, the getCheckedOut method is called to determine if the book has been checked out or not. getCheckedOut returns true if the book has been checked out and false otherwise. If it is true, it is set to false using the setCheckedOut method and the book is successfully returned
        Parameters:
        book - the book to be returned
        Returns:
        true if book is returned, false otherwise

      • shiftArray

        public void shiftArray(Book[] books,
                       int index)
        Helper method to move the elements of the array one index down to remove the book from the array The book at the index needs to be removed. All elements to the right of it are moved one index to the left, eventually getting rid of the book at the index
        Parameters:
        books - the books array to be shifted
        index - the index of the book to be removed

      • sortArrayByNumber

        public void sortArrayByNumber(Book[] books)
        This method sorts the array by serial number
        Parameters:
        books - the books array to be sorted
